1. Variables are container for storing data values.
2. IN java there are many variables 

2.1 String - stores text , values are surronding by double quotes.
2.2 int - stores integer (whoe numbers) , wihout decimal such as 123 or -123.
2.3 float - stores floating point numbers , with decimals , such as 32.42 or -90.43
2.4 char - stores single char , such as 'a' or 'B', surronding by single quotes
2.5 boolean - stores value true or false

